A '''first-degree relative''' is one's offspring, sibling or parent.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Talley|first1=Nicholas|title=Gastroenterology and Hepatology: A Clinical Handbook|date=2007|page=200}}</ref> It constitutes a category of family members that largely overlaps with the term [[nuclear family]], but without spouses.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Reiss|first1=David|title=The Family's Construction of Reality|date=1981|page=276}}</ref> First-degree relatives are a common measure used to diagnose risks for common diseases by analyzing family history.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Ginsburg|first1=Geoffrey|title=Genomic and Personalized Medicine, Volumes 1-2|date=2008|page=482}}</ref>

